%N A393952 Decimal expansion of Product_{p prime} ((1 + Sum_{k>=0} 1/(p^(2^(k+1)) + 2*p^(2^k))) * (1-1/p)^2 * Product_{k>=0} (1 + 2/p^(2^k))).
%C A393952 The asymptotic probability that the greatest common infinitary divisor of two positive integers selected independently at random is an exponentially 2^n-number (A138302).
%F A393952 Equals Product_{p prime} (1 + Sum_{k>=0} 1/(p^(2^(k+1)) + 2*p^(2^k))) * A393948.
%e A393952 0.994380928740398153030200247807975123997755498259925...
%o A393952 (PARI) c(m) = prodeulerrat(1 + sum(k = 0, m, 1/(p^(2^(k+1)) + 2*p^(2^k)))) * prodeulerrat((1 - 1/p)^2 * prod(k = 0, m, 1 + 2/p^(2^k)));
%o A393952 {my(c1 = 0, c2 = 1, m = 1); while(c2 != c1, c1 = c2; c2 = c(m); m++); c2}
%Y A393952 Cf. A077609, A138302.
%Y A393952 The asymptotic probability that the greatest common infinitary divisor of two positive integers selected independently at random is: A065472 (square), A393948 (1), A393949 (prime), A393950 (squarefree), A393951 (Fermi-Dirac prime), this constant (exponentially 2^n-number), A393953 (4th power).
